Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Feb 15, BNS -- Latvia's Cabinet empowered the 
country's delegation for talks with Russia Tuesday [15 February] 
to approve the Russian proposal on the functioning of the 
Skrunda radar. 
  Under the proposal, Russia will operate its early-warning 
radar station in Skrunda, Latvia, for four more years and 
dismantle it in 18 months after the term expires. In return, 
Russia pledges to complete its troop withdrawal by Aug. 31. 

